Rarras:

im still getting the same error lights

When you say error lights, what are the LEDs actually doing?

I would expect:

  • Alternating Orange when CAN connectivity is good but the Talon FX object doesn’t exist in code
  • Simultaneous blinking Orange when CAN connectivity is good and FX’s are declared in code but robot is disabled
  • Solid Orange when CAN is good, robot program is running, and robot is enabled.

I took a look at the User’s guide this morning and it looks like the above is not clear, so we’re going to try to update it as soon as we can.

I would recommend checking all of the basics (or double/triple checking, since you’ve probably already checked some of these):

  • Phoenix v5 vendordep in your code is latest (should be 5.30.4)
  • Firmware on Talon FX’s is latest v5 version (22.X firmware)
  • Code is properly deploying like you expect (are there any errors when you deploy to the robot? Does the code light in the Driver Station turn off and then on again when you deploy?)

Also from your description you have these plugged in to the roboRIO’s CAN bus, in which case your code looks correct. Just to double-check, you’re not using a CANivore, correct? If so you would need to change “rio” to be the name of the CANivore.

I would try to change your code to the following:

  private final WPI_TalonFX frontRightMotor = new WPI_TalonFX(4); 
  private final WPI_TalonFX rearRightMotor = new WPI_TalonFX(3); 
  private final WPI_TalonFX frontLeftMotor = new WPI_TalonFX(1); 
  private final WPI_TalonFX rearLeftMotor = new WPI_TalonFX(2);

  .....
  var speeds = DifferentialDrive.arcadeDriveIK(forwardMovement, rotatation, false);
  SmartDashboard.putNumber("Left", speeds.left);
  SmartDashboard.putNumber("Right", speeds.right);
  // Drive the Robot 
  //m_robotDrive.arcadeDrive(forwardMovement, rotatation);
  frontLeftMotor.set(ControlMode.PercentOutput, speeds.left);
  frontRightMotor.set(ControlMode.PercentOutput, speeds.right);
}

See if it changes anything for you. Also, have you verified that you can drive the motors via Phoenix Tuner?

Edit to add:
Then, if it’s still not working, check SmartDashboard values to verify that you are actually calculating and setting values.
